        <headline>Flood Advisory issued June 27 at 1:06PM CDT until June 27 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive
rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of West Tennessee, including the following
counties, Decatur, Hardin and Henderson.

* WHEN...Until 400 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 106 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. This will cause urban and small stream
flooding. Between 1 and 2.5 inches of rain have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 2 inches are expected over
the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Savannah, Parsons, Adamsville, Decaturville, Sardis, Morris
Chapel, Montgomery, Crump, Scotts Hill, Saltillo,
Milledgeville, Thurman, Pleasant Grove, Five Forks, Swift,
Dunbar, Red Walnut, Lick Skillet, Cerro Gordo and Haney.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.</instruction>
